        <.heading as="h1" class="font-display text-5xl/[0.9] font-medium tracking-tight text-balance text-gray-950 sm:text-6xl/[0.8] lg:text-7xl/[0.8] mb-8">
          Our Story
        </.heading>
        <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-gray-950/75 max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          From rebellion to evolution — how Eventasaurus became the future of event organizing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </.hero_section>

    <%!-- Opening Story Section --%>
    <.section class="py-24">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <.subheading class="mb-6 text-blue-600">The Beginning</.subheading>
        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 mb-8 font-medium">
            Eventasaurus didn't start with a business plan. It started with a rebellion.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-8">
            Born from a partnership with Unsound Festival — the internationally renowned music and arts 
            platform best known for its flagship event in Kraków and satellite editions across New York, 
            London, Toronto, Adelaide, Tbilisi, Brussels, and beyond — we launched festiment in 2019. 
            Together, we built a festival ticketing system from scratch, one designed to liberate events 
            from the grip of giant platforms like Ticketmaster. We wanted to put control back in the 
            hands of organizers, not middlemen.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </.section>

    <%!-- Festament Era Section with Image --%>
    <.section background="gradient" class="py-24">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <.subheading class="mb-6 text-blue-600">The festiment Era</.subheading>
          <.heading as="h2" class="mb-8 text-3xl sm:text-4xl">
            Building something different
          </.heading>
          <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              Festiment quickly grew beyond ticketing. We began powering entire festival ecosystems — 
              from managing artist schedules to handling guest lists — always focused on independent 
              and mid-sized events that deserved better tools than the corporate giants were offering.
            </p>
            <p>
              Every line of code was written with a simple belief: events should belong to their creators, 
              not to platforms that extract value while adding complexity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="relative">
          <img 
            src="/images/marketing/dino-revolution.png" 
            alt="Dinosaur revolution illustration representing building something different" 
            class="rounded-2xl shadow-xl border border-gray-200"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
          />
          <div class="absolute inset-0 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-t from-black/20 to-transparent"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </.section>

    <%!-- The Resistance Section --%>
